## Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio
Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Equity

Debt to Equity Ratio = $2,491,297.55 / $11,598,563.11 = 0.2148 ≈ 0.21

## Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

- Net Profit = -$1,401,436.89 (from income statement)
- Total Revenue = $7,825,951.24 (from income statement)

Net Profit Margin = (-$1,401,436.89 / $7,825,951.24) × 100% = -17.91%

## Step 3: Calculate Return on Assets (ROA)
ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%

- Net Profit = -$1,401,436.89 (from income statement)
- Total Assets = $14,089,860.66 (from balance sheet)

ROA = (-$1,401,436.89 / $14,089,860.66) × 100% = -9.95%

## Step 4: Calculate Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio
Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable

- Total Revenue = $7,825,951.24 (from income statement)
- Beginning Accounts Receivable = $0 (from balance sheet initial amount)
- Ending Accounts Receivable = $1,988,616.02 (from balance sheet end amount)
- Average Accounts Receivable = ($0 + $1,988,616.02) / 2 = $994,308.01

Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = $7,825,951.24 / $994,308.01 = 7.87
